ol.li: Maximum load on SPI_CK, SPI_CE, SPI_DATA is 32 pF
Minimum load on SPI_CK, SPI_CE, SPI_DATA is 2 pF
Maximum and minimum input transition on SPI_DATA is 2 ns and 0.5 ns respectively
The clock, chip select and output data trace length needs to be balanced
Micron/Winbond/Macronix NOR flash 100 MHz operation can be supported on SPI interface 1 (maximum trace length is dependent on dielectric material)
Micron/Winbond (reduced trace length) NOR flash and NVSRAM is supported on SPI interface 2
Does not support Macronix with 30pF load (8ns clock to Q delay). The Macronix clock to Q delay for 15 pF load is 6ns which can be supported
Another restriction is for NvSRAM 40 MHz operation. For NvSRAM 40 MHz operation, the SPI core clock frequency has to be less than or equal to 200 MHz to meet tslch parameter
